 BEIJING, June 6 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Dozens of elderly people were reported trapped on Wednesday after a building collapsed in Leshan in China's southwestern province of Sichuan, Xinhua news agency said. "Rescuers have removed more than 30 survivors, who have been sent to three hospitals, from the debris, but no deaths have been reported," said a spokesman for the city's public security bureau. Leshan is a popular tourist destination famed for its Grand Buddha, carved into a cliff face and standing more than 70 metres high. The former agriculture exhibition centre in downtown Leshan collapsed at around 7.20 am when at least 100 people, mostly old people, were inside to attend a lecture, a witness told Xinhua. One witness said he saw people running out of the building, their clothes covered in dust. The two-storey exhibition centre was built in 1959. It is largely unused
